13/08/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- On Tuesday (12 August), President Boris Trajkovski hailed the progress Macedonia has made in the two years since the signing of Ohrid Peace Accord. In a speech commemorating the 2nd anniversary of the accord, which ended the conflict between government forces and ethnic Albanian rebels, Trajkovski reiterated that "all participants in the Ohrid negotiations were acting in a responsible and wise manner, in total compliance with the long-term interests of the country and the future of all its citizens." He insisted that implementation of the agreement is the only path to achieving EU membership. (MIA, A1 TV - 12/08/03)
